[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Spring-test dependencies**\n\nI'm considering inspecting optional dependencies for the Spring-test POM, like servlet, hamcrest, testng, junit, xmlunit, and HtmlUnit. Tests may need explicit dependencies depending on the features used. The typical generated scaffold likely only includes the library and possibly JUnit. While the existing setup includes spring-context and junit, I need to decide if additional setup is necessary for achieving meaningful coverage. Since current in-memory unit tests may suffice, I’m wondering about the need for the extra spring-context dependency in version 7.0.0.\n\n**Exploring dependencies for Spring-test**\n\nI'm wondering if a deterministic setup can be applied before generating the build.gradle for fixing existing issues. I need to check if spring-test is usually used with spring-context. It seems the TestContext framework works with ApplicationContext, which does rely on spring-context. The spring-test POM doesn’t directly depend on it, so for meaningful coverage, I may need to include spring-context as well. The current setup already has it, and I should consider specifying the exact version. I might also need the jakarta.servlet-api for MockMvc and web app resources.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d4dfb948ade5def016a28de4f64048190944e6098236b1250\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKN5aSDQk_45xwMeA9sylb4OSxJ9ovZHyFwMWgbCoeD_3LA5P8M02_5c95u73Dg6PflhInoHybPLWlnBLsL8w0cWoWTcqaQwSf-ujzOsgNvhMpUGkuiCVMDi-yIyx_I7Hjm_h5CVpsd--wQGCR5wEkLa1roA0U4SOk3-N0jsXRv86Kc7Z6es7UvBUlIkgpQAxHOJ5YqE2fbICB4nJvUhlDgSSk9WhD-weaGDtXlOP0yzl90_5E8a2y6oV3mscGnjbG5Qc4FczuEHspZtUW6snx5IxjbHkX6HMZ9tatmJ0s4IbWIu-O31gBCGv57r4kRXvte4_vrabJQW4zOZE3rkaHli_jaQwSgPXICdNe-5xpf3SaPpsBiiIKEY5asBMhbh3dbDgLe6wx-7_M1dIsTOGTJv87H3ifhgGYQSd7YqB_mnbEl3C8049U1SnDPbcfjd_thR6jiuwrzwNwXj7UPm5QY-7pOxAPtMM-Hiqpd7_403o1IbzoE