s JUnit automatically, but I’m puzzled about the vintage JUnit and whether adding spring-context is essential. Should I suggest including spring-web/jakarta.servlet-api for thorough coverage?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating test failures**\\n\\nI'm looking into why the existing failure path uses WebAppConfiguration while lacking spring-web and jakarta.servlet. It seems to compile, possibly because WebAppConfiguration doesn’t require those dependencies. To fix the failing test, I’m wondering if we can avoid adding extra dependencies. I guess I need to check the documentation for guidance. Maybe using curl on my local setup could help confirm it, even if that detail doesn’t end up in the final solution.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_isWAX6CDIGNLsZoOnk9UTOi3|fc_0d4dfb948ade5def016a28de83ce70819088f40f4f2673ad8b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurls = [\n 'https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/reference/testing.html',\n 'https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/reference/testing/testcontext-framework.html',\n 'https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/reference/testing/mockmvc.html'\n]\nfor u in urls:\n print('URL', u)\n try:\n  data=urllib.request.urlopen(u, timeout=10).read(2000).decode('utf-8','ignore')\n  print(data[:500].replace('\\n',' ') )\n except Exception as e:\n  print('ERR', e)\nPY", "timeout": 40}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1839, "output": 617, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24472, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781063283367, "responseId": "resp_0d4dfb948ade5def016a28de73e56c8190a0f082f3252ee242"}}
